Remove the @sirloin steak{12%ounce} from the refrigerator and allow to come to room temperature. Bring a #medium pot{} of water to a boil with a large pinch of @salt{pinch}. Halve, seed, and chop the @tomato{1}. Mince the @shallot{1}(minced) and @parsley{1%bunch}(minced). Trim and halve the @green beans{4%ounce} and @wax beans{2%ounce}. Drain and rinse the @cannellini beans{1%12oz can}.

Blanch and shock the beans: fill a #medium bowl{} with ice water. Add the green beans and wax beans to the boiling water and cook for about ~{3%minutes}, until crisp-tender. Remove from water with a #slotted spoon{} and transfer to the ice water to shock them.

Make the vinaigrette: in a #small bowl{}, whisk together the minced shallot and parsley with @white wine vinegar{2%tablespoon} and @olive oil{2%tablespoon}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Drain the green beans and wax beans from the ice water and discard the water. In the same #bowl{}, toss the green beans, wax beans, cannellini beans, and the tomato with the vinaigrette. Season with salt and pepper and set aside to marinate.

Heat @olive oil{1/2%tablespoon} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Season the steak on all sides with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and the @herbes de Provence{1%teaspoon}. Sear the steak ~{5-7%minutes} per side, until cooked to desired doneness. Set aside for ~{5%minutes} to rest.

> This would be a great time to get a head start on cleanup!

Thinly slice the steak against the grain, then serve alongside the three-bean salad. Enjoy!

> For more tips on cooking the perfect steak, visit: Blog.HelloFresh.com